{"word":"ἀνάπαυλα","slug":"ἀνάπαυλα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀνάπαυλα</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀναπαύω'><el>ἀναπαύω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>repose, rest</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>κατ' ἀναπαύλας διηιρῆσθαι</el> to be divided into <i>reliefs</i>, of workmen, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> rei, <i>rest from</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a resting-place, an inn</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>deversorium</el>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}